transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm calling because I sent in an email like a month or two ago requesting to cancel my—

Speaker 2: Subscription.

Speaker 1: I tried to do it through my PayPal, they said they can't, they have to go directly to you.

Speaker 2: I have a response from you guys, your request, 398870 has to be received or whatever, but—

Speaker 1: I just checked today and they keep charging my card.

Speaker 2: I mean, what do I need to do to cancel that because I had a medical condition.

Speaker 1: I mean, we usually send you back an email that says to call us to cancel, that's—

Speaker 2: A pretty simple process.

Speaker 1: What's going on with Niagara though?

Speaker 2: Is it not working or are you just getting it too fast because you can order this as—

Speaker 1: Needed?

Speaker 2: No, a few months ago I had a medical condition, I had to go to the doctor and they told me—

Speaker 1: Do not take it anymore.

Speaker 2: I got like two orders sitting in my drawer there, can I use it, the doctor said don't—

Speaker 1: Take it anymore.

Speaker 2: So I got running some tests and see what was happening, I was in the hospital.

Speaker 1: So like two months ago, I tell them, you know, cancel it, you know, and I'm in a bad condition—

Speaker 2: I can't use it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, because we don't do cancellations through email.

Speaker 2: Okay, so how can I do the cancellation?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'll call and cancel it for you right now.

Speaker 2: I mean, your health doesn't matter.

Speaker 1: Yeah, right now.

Speaker 2: I understand.

Speaker 1: You can't take it.

Speaker 2: Cancel it, man, because I'm spending my money and it's just sitting in my drawer there—

Speaker 1: I can't even use this.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, no, we understand.

Speaker 1: So we canceled it for you.

Speaker 2: Is there anything else that you need?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: Will I get a confirmation email regarding that?

Speaker 1: No email, no, just the verbal confirmation.

Speaker 2: Is your prescription canceled?

Speaker 1: So verbally, it's canceled.

Speaker 2: What's your name?

Speaker 1: You have an agent name, a number or something?

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name is Quinn.

Speaker 1: No employee number or nothing like that?

Speaker 2: Yeah, extension is 0035.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: 0035.

Speaker 2: Glenn.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much, Glenn.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: You have a good day.
